(41, 5, 8, 41, 1, 25, 25, NULL, 'Exorcism Commands by Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus commanding unclean spirits to leave individuals. The phrases ''come out of him'' and ''come out of the man'' highlight His authority over evil spirits.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 8, 41, 9, 25, 26, 'Come out of the man, thou unclean spirit.', 'Connection of Unclean Spirits', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' authority over unclean spirits. In Mark 5:8, Jesus commands an unclean spirit to come out, while in Mark 9:25-26, he rebukes a foul spirit and commands it to leave. This connection highlights the consistent theme of Jesus'' power in exorcisms.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 8, 44, 16, 18, 18, 'Come out of the man, thou unclean spirit', 'Exorcism Command Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the command to expel unclean spirits. In Mark, Jesus commands the spirit to come out, while in Acts, Paul similarly commands the spirit to leave in Jesus'' name.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 9, 42, 8, 30, 30, 'My name is Legion: for we are many.', 'Connection of Demonic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the name ''Legion'' as a representation of many demons within a single individual. This connection highlights the shared theme of demonic possession and the identity of the possessed man.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 9, 41, 5, 15, 15, NULL, 'Possession and Restoration', 'This connection highlights the transformation of the man possessed by a legion of demons. In the first passage, he identifies himself as ''Legion,'' and in the second, he is found ''clothed'' and ''in his right mind,'' indicating a complete restoration.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 9, 40, 26, 53, 53, 'Legion: for we are many', 'Legion as a Symbol of Power', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''Legion'' as a representation of a multitude, whether in demonic forces or angelic beings. Both passages emphasize the power associated with the term ''Legion'' in contrasting contexts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 9, 40, 12, 45, 45, 'for we are many', 'Connection of Wicked Spirits', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of multiple spirits. In Mark, the term ''Legion'' signifies many spirits, while Matthew describes a man being possessed by ''seven other spirits more wicked.'' This connection highlights the theme of increasing spiritual oppression.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 9, 42, 11, 21, 26, 'My name is Legion: for we are many', 'Connection of Demonic Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of multiple unclean spirits. In Mark, the man is possessed by a ''Legion'' of demons, while in Luke, a spirit returns with seven others, illustrating the theme of spiritual warfare and possession.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 10, 41, 3, 22, 22, NULL, 'Demons and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of demons and their desire to remain in a specific location. In Mark 5:10, the demons plead not to be sent away, while in Mark 3:22, the scribes accuse Jesus of casting out demons by the power of Beelzebub, indicating a struggle over demonic authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 10, 41, 5, 13, 13, 'not send them away out of the country', 'Request of the Unclean Spirits', 'This connection highlights the plea of the unclean spirits in Mark 5:10, where they ask Jesus not to send them away. In Mark 5:13, Jesus grants them permission, allowing them to enter the swine, which illustrates the fulfillment of their request.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 11, 3, 11, 7, 8, 'a great herd of swine', 'Connection of Swine in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the presence of swine in both passages. Mark 5:11 mentions a herd of swine, while Leviticus 11:7-8 describes swine as unclean animals, emphasizing their significance in biblical dietary laws.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 11, 5, 14, 8, 8, 'a great herd of swine feeding', 'Connection of Swine in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the presence of swine in both passages. Mark 5:11 mentions a herd of swine, while Deuteronomy 14:8 classifies swine as unclean animals.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 11, 23, 65, 4, 4, 'swine', 'Connection of Swine References', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of swine, linking the feeding herd in Mark to the consumption of swine''s flesh in Isaiah. This connection highlights the cultural and ritual implications of swine in biblical texts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
